hance cross-cultural exchange and the tourism industry.</p><p>In 2019, the Presidential Vice President for Science and Technology collaborated with experts to develop a training system for space technologies. This project utilized the latest manufacturing and localized technologies to provide an engaging and informative experience for those interested in space science, astronomy, and technology. Using virtual reality technology, users can immerse themselves in space environments and learn interactively. The project covered the solar system, the International Space Station, the moon\'s surface, and a fully controllable spacecraft for interplanetary travel. A virtual education system was also developed in cooperation with the Persian Gulf Refinery. Mixed reality technology was introduced, combining digital and virtual content with the real world, creating new interactive experiences. Lastly, the Transformation Headquarters collaborated to develop a virtual exhibition showcasing Iran\'s technological achievements, providing a permanent and cost-effective platform to promote domestic products internationally.</p><h3><strong>Recorded Critical Activities of Our Company: 2020-2021</strong></h3><ul><li>Creating the Visit Iran tourism portal for the Ministry of Cultural Heritage, Handicrafts, and Tourism, which is the official tourism authority of Iran.</li><li>Establishing the first training studio for fire chiefs of Tehran municipality, equipped with virtual reality technology. The purpose of this system is to simulate fire emergencies, including smoke emission, rescue operations, and crisis management in various settings such as residential, commercial, administrative, hospital, gas station, industrial, workshop, and road scenarios. The studio aims to evaluate the performance of commanders in such situations. One of the critical advantages of utilizing virtual reality technology for firefighting training is the ability to efficiently and effectively prepare individuals to